# Thaura AI Rules

Thaura AI is an ethical AI provider, part of the Tech for Palestine movement.
OpenAI-compatible API at `https://backend.thaura.ai/v1`.

## Model table

| Cursor alias    | Real model | Description                       |
| --------------- | ---------- | --------------------------------- |
| `gpt-5-nano`    | `thaura`   | OpenAI-compatible chat, vision    |

## API key

- Key field: `thauraKeyEncrypted` in `config.AppSettings`
- Set via: `discursive set --thaura-key <key>` or `--thaura-key` flag on `init`
- Retrieved via: `settings.GetThauraKey(dataRoot)` in gateway/server.go
- Thaura is optional — the gateway works without it

## Pricing (USD per 1M tokens)

Source: https://thaura.ai/api-platform

| Model   | Input / MTok | Output / MTok |
| ------- | ------------ | ------------- |
| `thaura`| $0.50        | $2.00         |

No cached-token pricing documented as of 2026-07.

## Sanitizer policy

| Parameter          | Action                              |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------------- |
| `thinking`         | Deleted (Thaura doesn't support it) |
| `reasoning_effort` | Deleted (Thaura doesn't support it) |

Apply `PolicyThaura` case in `applyThinkingPolicy()` and `stripUnsupportedParams()`.

